76561198155109554,Recommended,282400,33711778,Posted: 21 July,all,Subfusca,"Iso nearlydidn't buy this game. But I'm so glad that I did. I was looking for something of a certain kind of niche genre, and it sounded like SuperPower 2 was exactly what I was looking for. But then I started reading the reviews, and read through the first few pages, which at the time were filled with mostly negative ones, speaking of a game that was mortally wounded by utterly game-breaking bugs and frequent crashes.Disappointed, I continued my search for other games. I came across a few that sounded promising; RealPolitik, GPS etc, but once again, reading the reviews, it seemed that desite their grand intentions -- all of these great sounding titles were fatally flawed with varying degrees of gameplay issues.A few days later, I still felt the pull towards SP2, and came back for another read. I don't know if it was (unintentionally) my settings, but this time the first few pages were full of mostly positive reviews, which led me to the discovery of the Realism2016 mod, and that the vast majority of all those bugs I'd read about had actually long since been fixed by a dedicated modding community. So I took the plunge, and gave it a try.I'm in the year 2147 currently, playing as Palestine -- and I'm delighted to report that my game has not crashed at all at any point. Not one single crash, or any game-breaking bugs in sight. Theworstthing that I've seen occur so far, is when moving units around on the map, maybe they don't always end upexactlywhere I wanted them, but seriously, it's a minimal margin of error on most occasions, and certainly not something that cannot be easily lived with, when considering all that this game gives back for the investment of your time. And it will certainly guzzle up large portions of that, if you let it. ;)  It is extremely immersive, and an engaging musical score really adds to the feeling of playing.This game's depth and complexity is majestic. If you enjoy a game that asks for a lot of investment from you in your attention to the finest of details in order to be truly successful - but rewards you in great measure for your efforts - then I'd imagine you'll derive a lot of enjoyment from SuperPower 2. I have found it to be thoroughly absorbing, and you can become so deeply involved within it, that hours of (real) time have slipped by almost unnoticed.Due to its vast intricacies, this is primarily a game for intelligent, patient and thoughtful people if you really want to get the most out of it; but then if all you want to do is just jump straight into inflaming a global thermonuclear war, to hell with the economy and all your people who empower it -- and everything else is simply extraneous collateral damage -- well, I guess there's even something in it for you too. ;)  But why you would wish to destroy such a beautifully rendered interactive world, I cannot fathom. :)TLDR: Don't be put off by the many negative reviews that write this game off as broken and unplayable. With the dedicated modding community working to keep this great classic game up to date, all major game-breaking bugs have been fixed, and from the time of writing in the (gametime) year 2147 - not had a single crash so far. The game works almost perfectly (show me one that isever100% bug-free?), at least on this windows 7 machine anyway.A very deep and complex game which can offer you endless hours of enjoyment if you're prepared to invest in learning the underlying mechanisms of effectively operating the State Machinery; or -- if you just want to blow sh*t up -- there is plenty of fun to be had there for you too. ;)Directions: Purchase. Update with theRealism2016mod. Enjoy."
