76561198041736274,Recommended,282400,10003867,"Posted: 2 May, 2014",all,Texas Toast,"Wow, this game is fantastic, hands-down THE best RTS I've played. My friend says that he'd play it over DEFCON, and with good reason. It's an RTS that has a great combination of economic, political, and military control for any nation of your choosing (The game takes place in the year 2001 though, so some nations may not have up-to-date flags, territory control, etc.).Pros:-Play as ANY nation. Some nations are harder to develop than others, but if you'd like to make Nepal or Sierra Leone a world superpower, then you can do it.-Game makes you feel like you're actually running a country. Multiple layers of depth are found under economy, politics, and military tabs. You can control things as intricate as raising taxes of vegetables and fruit for your nation.-The battle system is pretty well designed, with multiple types of vehicles with different uses and statistics. You can even design your own mechanical weapons.-If you manage to find a multiplayer roleplay server, the experience is greatCons:-The game doesn't come in full screen. It's not a huge issue to me, but devs said they're working on it for those who do mind.-The AI can act a little funky sometimes. Nations will sometimes declare war on nations 2 continents away for no reason.-I didn't find the game to be easily moddable, such as when I tried to install a ""modern-day setting"" mod that crashed the game upon startup. Maybe I did it wrong.-The multiplayer server lobby is glitched, with servers not being taken off the list despite them being shut down. I recommend going to the game's discussion site to find multiplayer servers.The game is well worth the $10, and devs are currently working on fixing some bugs it has, so I'm looking forward to playing more.9/10"
